m_q.target_metric: Maximum total acres burned in any 3-month consecutive period since January 2000
sub_questions: What is the date range format in the Date column?
How to parse Date column (format: YYYYMM)?
How to create rolling 3-month windows from monthly data?
What is the sum of Acres Burned for each 3-month window?
Which 3-month period has the maximum total Acres Burned?
What is the total Acres Burned value for that period?

format_notes: Date column is integer format YYYYMM (e.g., 200001 = January 2000)
noaa_wildfires_monthly_stats__section_1 contains metadata indicating missing values coded as -999

constraints: Only include data from January 2000 onwards (Date >= 200001)
Each 3-month window should roll forward by 1 month
Date must be properly sorted chronologically
derived_filters: Filter out any records with Date < 200001
Exclude any rows where Acres Burned = -999 (sentinel value for missing data)
output_format_requirements: Report the starting month-year of the 3-month period with highest acres burned
Report the total acres burned as an integer or float value
Clearly identify which 3 consecutive months comprise the period
